race.comment: EL TERCERO (7) found a soft track and was back to his best beaten 1.2L at Geelong in a 70. Meech rides and will position him handy. Should be near peak and is suited back in grade. DOLLAR SHOT (2) was on speed at Sale and returned to the winners' list this grade/trip. Nash Rawiller is a key jockey switch and will likely push forward. Will be suited around here and briefly freshened is sure to feature. IMMORTAL STAR (8) resumes and has switched to the Ciaron Maher yard. She's raced three times at Group level and John Allen is booked. Should find a good position in running and can be in the finish. LYGON STREET LUIGI (9) resumes and has placed 4/5 fresh. Went close in town his last two and won a recent Flemington jumpout. Keep very safe.
